<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Protocol No 9 provides for a special regime concerning the transit of heavy goods vehicles through Austrian territory based on a system of Rights of Transit (ecopoints). </inglise>
<eesti> 1) protokolliga nr 9 n&auml;hakse ette Austria territooriumi kaudu kulgevat raskete kaubaveokite transiiti k&auml;sitlev erire&zcaron;iim, mis p&otilde;hineb transiidi&otilde;iguste s&uuml;steemil (&ouml;kopunktide s&uuml;steemil). </eesti>
<inglise> The distribution scale of ecopoints to the Member States is given by Annex 4 to the Protocol. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriikidele &ouml;kopunktide jaotamisskaala on esitatud selle protokolli lisas 4; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Article 11(2) c of Protocol No 9 requires the Commission to adopt appropriate measures in accordance with paragraph 3 of Annex 5 thereto if the number of transit journeys through Austria requiring ecopoints in any year exceeds the reference figure established for 1991 by more than 8 %. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) protokolli nr 9 artikli 11 l&otilde;ike 2 punktis c n&otilde;utakse, et komisjon peab v&otilde;tma kohased meetmed vastavalt selle lisa 5 punktile 3, kui &ouml;kopunkte n&otilde;udvate transiits&otilde;itude arv l&auml;bi Austria &uuml;letab mingil aastal 1991. aasta kontrollarvu enam kui 8%; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Paragraph 3 of Annex 5 to the Protocol lays down rules in order to establish a revised number of ecopoints that shall be made available in case the 1991 reference figure is exceeded. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) protokolli lisa 5 punktis 3 s&auml;testatakse l&auml;bivaatamise kord, mille alusel toimub &ouml;kopunktide eraldamine juhul, kui &uuml;letatakse 1991. aasta kontrollarv; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) The threshold established in the abovementioned Article 11(2) c was exceeded in 1999. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) 1999. aastal &uuml;letati eespool nimetatud artikli 11 l&otilde;ike 2 punktis c kehtestatud k&uuml;nnis. </eesti>
<inglise> The application of the calculation method laid down by paragraph 3 of Annex 5 will lead to a reduction of the overall number of available ecopoints. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisa 5 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud arvutusmeetodi rakendamine viib olemasolevate &ouml;kopunktide &uuml;ldarvu v&auml;henemisele; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Protocol No 9 must be applied in accordance with the fundamental freedoms established by the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) protokolli nr 9 tuleb kohaldada koosk&otilde;las asutamislepingus s&auml;testatud p&otilde;hivabadustega. </eesti>
<inglise> It is therefore imperative to take measures which are capable of ensuring the free movement of goods and the full functioning of the internal market. </inglise>
<eesti> Seet&otilde;ttu on m&ouml;&ouml;dap&auml;&auml;smatu meetmete v&otilde;tmine, mis suudaksid tagada kaupade vaba liikumise ja siseturu t&auml;ieliku toimimise; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) To impose the whole reduction of ecopoints solely in 2000 would have the disproportionate effect of stopping, to all intents and purposes, transit traffic through Austria. </inglise>
<eesti> 6) &ouml;kopunktide &uuml;ldarvu v&auml;hendamise kehtestamine ainult 2000. aastal omaks disproportsionaalset m&otilde;ju, l&otilde;petades pea igasuguse transiitliikluse l&auml;bi Austria. </eesti>
<inglise> As a result, the reduction in the total number of ecopoints should be spread over the years 2000 to 2003. </inglise>
<eesti> Selle t&otilde;ttu tuleks &ouml;kopunktide &uuml;ldarvu v&auml;hendamine jaotada aastatele 2000 kuni 2003; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Proportionality of the reduction of ecoponts also requires that those Member States who contributed most to the 8 % threshold being exceeded should have their allocations of ecopoints cut to ensure that the total reduction is met. </inglise>
<eesti> 7) seoses &ouml;kopunktide proportsionaalse v&auml;hendamisega on vajalik, et nendele liikmesriikidele, kelle panus 8% k&uuml;nnise &uuml;letamisel oli k&otilde;ige suurem, eraldataks &uuml;ldarvu v&auml;hendamise tagamiseks v&auml;hem &ouml;kopunkte. </eesti>
<inglise> This calls for a revision of the distribution key of ecopoints to the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> See tingib liikmesriikidele &ouml;kopunktide jaotamise aluse l&auml;bivaatamise; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) To ensure the most efficient use of the available number of ecopoints, measures shall be undertaken further to encourage Member States to return unused ecopoints to the Commission for redistribution. </inglise>
<eesti> 8) olemasolevate &ouml;kopunktide k&otilde;ige t&otilde;husama kasutamise tagamiseks v&otilde;etakse meetmed, millega ergutatakse liikmesriike tagastama oma kasutamata &ouml;kopunktid komisjonile &uuml;mberjaotamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) More intensive use of rail freight in combined transport, in particular of the "Rollende Landstra&szlig;e", is less environmentally damaging than road freight and has the potential of relieving the pressure on the number of ecopoints available. </inglise>
<eesti> 9) kombineeritud vedude korral on raudteevedude, eelk&otilde;ige "Rollende Landstra&szlig;e" intensiivsem kasutamine keskkonda v&auml;hem kahjustav kui autovedude korral ning see v&otilde;ib v&auml;hendada pinget seoses olemasolevate &ouml;kopunktide arvuga. </eesti>
<inglise> Its more efficient use, inter alia by reviewing the way in which places are reserved, should be urgently promoted. </inglise>
<eesti> Tuleks tungivalt edendada selle t&otilde;husamat kasutamist, vaadates muu hulgas l&auml;bi, kuidas kohti reserveeritakse. </eesti>
<inglise> The effects of such efforts should be monitored. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealuste meetmete m&otilde;ju tuleks j&auml;lgida; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Annex 4 to Protocol No 9 and Commission Regulation (EC) No 3298/94(1) should be amended accordingly. </inglise>
<eesti> 10) sellest tulenevalt tuleks muuta protokolli nr 9 lisa 4 ja m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 3298/94; (1) </eesti>
